<Issue id="39447" key="IS-1245" number="1245" project="10401" reporter="sergey.minaev" assignee="artemkaaas" creator="sergey.minaev" type="10006" summary="CLI should provide the way to multisign any transaction" priority="3" resolution="10000" status="10001" created="2019-04-23 12:01:49.0" updated="2019-06-12 00:41:19.0" resolutiondate="2019-05-10 09:08:07.0" votes="0" watches="2" workflowId="52326"> <description><! CDATA It needs to be possible to add signatures to an existing transaction without requiring cut-and-paste the text  *Acceptance Criteria* The CLI needs to be able to: * Generate a transaction without submitting it to the ledger. * Allow the transaction to be saved as a text file. * Import a transaction from a text file. * Append a signature to an existing transaction.  *Notes* I'm picturing a user interaction like: {code}  bash % indy-cli >>> wallet load >>> select did >>> load-transaction t.txt >>> . . . add our signature >>> save-transaction t2.txt {code}  ></description> </Issue>
